1
00:00:23,750 --> 00:00:26,083
[DAGGER]
Ladies and gentlemen of BRR.

2
00:00:26,166 --> 00:00:29,375
Once again, this is
a declaration of war.

3
00:00:31,625 --> 00:00:34,000
[ROSIA]
Man! I'm starving!

4
00:00:34,083 --> 00:00:35,250
[CYAN]
Rosia.

5
00:00:35,333 --> 00:00:36,833
What's going on? Why do
you all look so worried?

6
00:00:36,916 --> 00:00:39,750
[DAGGER]
Hello, Rosia. Long time no see.

7
00:00:39,833 --> 00:00:41,083
[gasps]

8
00:00:41,166 --> 00:00:42,250
[DAGGER]
Don't worry.

9
00:00:42,333 --> 00:00:45,166
I'm not concerned with
you girls anymore.

10
00:00:45,250 --> 00:00:46,541
[gasps]

11
00:00:46,625 --> 00:00:48,875
[DAGGER] I'm here to
inform you my colleagues

12
00:00:48,958 --> 00:00:51,666
from BVL wish to
challenge Plasmagica

13
00:00:51,750 --> 00:00:53,375
to a battle of the bands.

14
00:00:53,458 --> 00:00:55,416
Will you stand tall
and accept it?

15
00:00:55,500 --> 00:00:59,208
Or run away and hide like
a bunch of scared cats?

16
00:00:59,291 --> 00:01:01,041
The countdown to
the glorious day

17
00:01:01,125 --> 00:01:03,291
of your misfortune has begun.

18
00:01:03,375 --> 00:01:05,000
Struggle all you want.

19
00:01:05,083 --> 00:01:11,250
[DAGGER cackles]

20
00:01:16,125 --> 00:01:17,708
[MAPLE]
He finally came, huh?

21
00:01:17,791 --> 00:01:18,958
That bastard!

22
00:01:19,041 --> 00:01:20,875
You know, for someone
as tiny as he is now,

23
00:01:20,958 --> 00:01:22,833
he's sure got a big mouth!

24
00:01:22,916 --> 00:01:24,458
What are you gonna do, Prez?

25
00:01:24,541 --> 00:01:26,875
[MAPLE]
Hm. What do ya think?

26
00:01:26,958 --> 00:01:28,583
You girls up for it?

27
00:01:28,666 --> 00:01:30,583
Of course! We accept
his challenge!

28
00:01:30,666 --> 00:01:32,375
You betcha, pyuru!

29
00:01:32,458 --> 00:01:33,416
And with Cyan,

30
00:01:33,500 --> 00:01:35,583
there's no way
Plasmagica can lose!

31
00:01:35,666 --> 00:01:36,833
Sure.

32
00:01:36,916 --> 00:01:39,833
[ROSIA whimpers]

33
00:01:39,916 --> 00:01:45,041
[DAGGER] You're worthless.
Complete trash!

34
00:01:45,125 --> 00:01:49,208
--And trash gets dumped!
--[GIRLS scream]

35
00:01:51,875 --> 00:01:54,333
[DAGGER] Goodnight, goodbye,
and good riddance!

36
00:01:54,416 --> 00:01:56,375
[screaming]

37
00:01:58,375 --> 00:01:59,166
[HOLMY]
Rosia?

38
00:01:59,250 --> 00:02:00,000
[gasps]

39
00:02:00,083 --> 00:02:01,750
Is everything all right?

40
00:02:01,833 --> 00:02:03,250
Uh, sure.

41
00:02:04,333 --> 00:02:06,791
[CYAN] Don't worry,
Rosia. It'll be fine.

42
00:02:06,875 --> 00:02:08,833
We won't let something
scary like what went down

43
00:02:08,916 --> 00:02:11,291
before happen again, okay?

44
00:02:11,375 --> 00:02:13,333
Cyan, you're the best.

45
00:02:15,541 --> 00:02:18,750
So that band is called BVL, huh?

46
00:02:18,833 --> 00:02:20,041
No matter how much I search,

47
00:02:20,125 --> 00:02:22,125
I can't find out
anything about them.

48
00:02:22,208 --> 00:02:24,250
I don't like going in blind.

49
00:02:24,333 --> 00:02:25,666
[CHUCHU]
Me, either.

50
00:02:25,750 --> 00:02:27,625
Still, no matter what kind of
music they come up with

51
00:02:27,708 --> 00:02:29,833
for Midi City--scratch that!

52
00:02:29,916 --> 00:02:32,208
For Sound Planet,
we've just gotta win!

53
00:02:32,291 --> 00:02:34,000
Everyone's depending on us!

54
00:02:34,083 --> 00:02:36,250
For the sake of
Pyuru Land, too, pyuru!

55
00:02:36,333 --> 00:02:37,708
[BOTH]
Yeah!

56
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:50,000
♪

57
00:02:54,208 --> 00:02:57,166
[PLASMAGICA]
♪ Go! Go! Go! Go! Go! Go! ♪

58
00:02:57,250 --> 00:02:58,500
♪ Pumping Jumping! ♪

59
00:02:58,583 --> 00:03:01,583
♪ Go! Go! Go! Go! Go! Go! ♪

60
00:03:01,666 --> 00:03:03,000
♪ Jump to the beat! Hey! ♪

61
00:03:03,083 --> 00:03:05,166
[CYAN] ♪ Dontcha come at me
with your monotone ♪

62
00:03:05,250 --> 00:03:07,333
♪ Feelin' somethin'
more harmonious ♪

63
00:03:07,416 --> 00:03:08,833
[CHUCHU]
♪ Waiting, to take a breath ♪

64
00:03:08,916 --> 00:03:11,375
♪ I look, listen,
oh so carefully ♪

65
00:03:11,458 --> 00:03:13,750
[RETOREE] ♪ Oh baby,
can you hear the chords ♪

66
00:03:13,833 --> 00:03:16,041
♪ Soundin' sweet the more
we rock the pop ♪

67
00:03:16,125 --> 00:03:17,958
[MOA] ♪ Let's mix and
match our swing now ♪

68
00:03:18,041 --> 00:03:21,041
♪ To make the music that we've
all been feelin' inside ♪

69
00:03:21,125 --> 00:03:24,375
[CYAN, CHUCHU] ♪ (Passhuwa!
Pappasshuwa! Pashuwa, yes!) ♪

70
00:03:24,458 --> 00:03:26,083
[CYAN]
♪ 'Cause even in my dreams ♪

71
00:03:26,166 --> 00:03:28,833
♪ I hear the sound
of your voice ♪

72
00:03:28,916 --> 00:03:32,833
[CHUCHU] ♪ In you I finally see
There is no other choice ♪

73
00:03:32,916 --> 00:03:35,375
[RETOREE] ♪ I know I can
keep pushing ahead ♪

74
00:03:35,458 --> 00:03:37,333
♪ And that I can really change ♪

75
00:03:37,416 --> 00:03:40,000
[MOA] ♪ All I need is
to find melodies ♪

76
00:03:40,083 --> 00:03:41,708
♪ I haven't
discovered just yet ♪

77
00:03:41,791 --> 00:03:44,250
[CYAN, CHUCHU] ♪ Everybody Rock!
Rock! Give it your all! ♪

78
00:03:44,333 --> 00:03:46,000
♪ Just sing and be yourself! ♪

79
00:03:46,083 --> 00:03:47,708
♪ Keep on keepin' on
and on and on and on ♪

80
00:03:47,791 --> 00:03:50,500
♪ and cramming emotions
into your music ♪

81
00:03:50,583 --> 00:03:53,041
♪ Everybody Rock! Rock!
With all your heart! ♪

82
00:03:53,125 --> 00:03:55,250
♪ And soon you'll
hear new melodies ♪

83
00:03:55,333 --> 00:03:56,166
♪ Hear the pulsing beat ♪

84
00:03:56,250 --> 00:03:57,708
♪ The power of the rhythm ♪

85
00:03:57,791 --> 00:03:59,375
♪ The magic never stops ♪

86
00:03:59,458 --> 00:04:02,125
[PLASMAGICA] ♪ All you need is
harmony (words don't matter) ♪

87
00:04:02,208 --> 00:04:04,250
♪ Honesty
(With your feelings) ♪

88
00:04:04,333 --> 00:04:06,875
♪ Keep on strumming! Keep on
going! Keep on and on! ♪

89
00:04:06,958 --> 00:04:09,791
♪ Go! Go! Go! Go! Go! Go! ♪

90
00:04:09,875 --> 00:04:11,458
♪ Jump to the beat! Hey! ♪

91
00:04:18,916 --> 00:04:27,166
[school bell rings]

92
00:04:31,625 --> 00:04:33,541
[ROSIA]
That girl.

93
00:04:33,625 --> 00:04:36,375
I wonder if she's
here again today.

94
00:04:44,125 --> 00:04:45,500
[sighs]

95
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:49,041
[ROSIA gasps]

96
00:04:49,125 --> 00:04:50,958
What do you think you're doing?

97
00:04:51,041 --> 00:04:53,041
You're not peeping
again, are you?

98
00:04:53,125 --> 00:04:54,458
[ROSIA whimpers]

99
00:04:57,916 --> 00:04:59,291
[PEIPAIN]
Either you hurry up and answer

100
00:04:59,375 --> 00:05:02,916
Master Ailane's question,
or I'll make you regret it.

101
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:05,250
My business is with that
little shorty, not you two!

102
00:05:05,333 --> 00:05:06,500
So just back off!

103
00:05:06,583 --> 00:05:09,000
[PEIPAIN] How can you
speak to us so rudely?

104
00:05:09,083 --> 00:05:11,500
You dare insult Master Ailane?

105
00:05:13,208 --> 00:05:15,541
I will not forgive
those who harm my master.

106
00:05:15,625 --> 00:05:18,791
And I have no patience
for brats like you.

107
00:05:18,875 --> 00:05:20,750
[ROSIA]
I-It's you guys, isn't it?

108
00:05:20,833 --> 00:05:22,250
You're the ones who
teamed up with Dagger

109
00:05:22,333 --> 00:05:24,958
and are taking on Plasmagica
in a battle of the bands!

110
00:05:25,041 --> 00:05:27,000
Could be. And what would
you plan on doing

111
00:05:27,083 --> 00:05:28,833
about it if that's true?

112
00:05:28,916 --> 00:05:31,625
Maybe... Look, I don't
know what your deal is,

113
00:05:31,708 --> 00:05:32,833
but if you're gonna
do something weird

114
00:05:32,916 --> 00:05:35,041
to Plasmagica's
Melodisians, then--!

115
00:05:35,125 --> 00:05:36,583
[AILANE]
Then what?

116
00:05:36,666 --> 00:05:38,333
[gasps]

117
00:05:38,416 --> 00:05:40,500
I'd think long and hard
about what you're gonna

118
00:05:40,583 --> 00:05:42,916
say to me, if I were you.

119
00:05:47,291 --> 00:05:48,875
[AILANE]
Hmph.

120
00:05:52,708 --> 00:05:54,041
[ROSIA]
Plasmagica would never lose

121
00:05:54,125 --> 00:05:55,750
to the likes of you people!

122
00:05:55,833 --> 00:05:58,000
You hear me? Never!

123
00:06:00,416 --> 00:06:02,583
[CHUCHU] Looks like the
time's finally come, y'all!

124
00:06:02,666 --> 00:06:05,416
Pyuru! We'll fight
with Cyan's new song!

125
00:06:05,500 --> 00:06:07,333
[RETOREE]
Let's lay it on 'em hardcore!

126
00:06:07,416 --> 00:06:08,166
Yeah!

127
00:06:08,250 --> 00:06:09,666
I was wonderin'.

128
00:06:09,750 --> 00:06:11,833
Is there anything the rest
of us can do to help you out?

129
00:06:11,916 --> 00:06:12,708
[CYAN]
Huh?

130
00:06:12,791 --> 00:06:14,916
How do you wanna do this, pyuru?

131
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:19,541
Well... First, I'll try
making a demo of my ideas!

132
00:06:19,625 --> 00:06:22,083
Sounds good! I can't
wait to hear them!

133
00:06:22,166 --> 00:06:23,458
Cool!

134
00:06:24,541 --> 00:06:27,833
Well, that's what I said
about it at the time, anyway,

135
00:06:27,916 --> 00:06:30,083
but I can't think of anything!

136
00:06:30,166 --> 00:06:31,875
[sighs]

137
00:06:31,958 --> 00:06:34,333
I have to write something
that's not only super catchy,

138
00:06:34,416 --> 00:06:36,375
but surprising, too.

139
00:06:39,541 --> 00:06:41,250
[CYAN]
Hey, Mr. Berry.

140
00:06:41,333 --> 00:06:43,958
I'm not getting any ideas here!

141
00:06:49,625 --> 00:06:52,041
This is no time to whine, Cyan!

142
00:06:52,125 --> 00:06:55,291
Everyone's counting on you,
so get it together!

143
00:06:55,375 --> 00:06:58,208
All right! I'll do my best!

144
00:07:24,416 --> 00:07:26,166
[gasps] I overslept!

145
00:07:26,250 --> 00:07:28,833
Practice already started and
I still don't have anything!

146
00:07:28,916 --> 00:07:30,291
I have to hurry!

147
00:07:33,166 --> 00:07:34,750
[CHUCHU]
If we're gonna beat them,

148
00:07:34,833 --> 00:07:37,083
then we should focus
on something positive.

149
00:07:37,166 --> 00:07:39,791
We need that kind of energy
to smash their darkness.

150
00:07:39,875 --> 00:07:42,291
Like Cyan did that
time before, pyuru.

151
00:07:42,375 --> 00:07:43,625
[CHUCHU]
That's right.

152
00:07:43,708 --> 00:07:45,291
We also need to work extra hard

153
00:07:45,375 --> 00:07:47,708
to further evolve
our Melodisians!

154
00:07:47,791 --> 00:07:51,250
I'm sure that Cyan will write
an amazing song for us!

155
00:07:51,333 --> 00:07:53,708
And we need to do our best
to bring that song to life!

156
00:07:53,791 --> 00:07:55,375
We don't wanna let Cyan down!

157
00:07:55,458 --> 00:07:57,333
--[MOA] Pyuru!
--[RETOREE] Yeah, let's do it!

158
00:07:57,416 --> 00:07:58,416
[CHUCHU]
Speaking of which.

159
00:07:58,500 --> 00:08:01,375
Where is she?
Cyan's never this late.

160
00:08:05,291 --> 00:08:07,291
[CYAN]
Can we really do this?

161
00:08:07,375 --> 00:08:10,916
Can we win with a new
song written by me?

162
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:12,125
[door opens]

163
00:08:12,208 --> 00:08:13,458
[MOA]
Hey! There you are!

164
00:08:13,541 --> 00:08:14,666
We were worried, pyuru!

165
00:08:14,750 --> 00:08:15,916
Yeah, you're really late.

166
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:17,625
We were about to go find you.

167
00:08:17,708 --> 00:08:19,583
Oh! Sorry!

168
00:08:19,666 --> 00:08:22,333
Guess I got caught up
in the writing!

169
00:08:22,416 --> 00:08:23,708
Whoa, you look tired.

170
00:08:23,791 --> 00:08:24,666
Feelin' okay?

171
00:08:24,750 --> 00:08:25,916
Have you slept?

172
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:28,000
You weren't awake all
night writing, were you?

173
00:08:28,083 --> 00:08:29,333
[nervously giggles]

174
00:08:29,416 --> 00:08:31,458
[CHUCHU] You need to take
better care of yourself!

175
00:08:31,541 --> 00:08:32,916
Not only for your well-being,

176
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:35,583
but they say wonderful songs
come from healthy bodies!

177
00:08:35,666 --> 00:08:37,541
And healthy bodies
are made of yummy,

178
00:08:37,625 --> 00:08:39,750
delicious food, pyuru!

179
00:08:41,291 --> 00:08:42,416
[CHUCHU]
I've got an idea!

180
00:08:42,500 --> 00:08:43,916
There's supposed to be
a new burger place

181
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:46,291
that just opened up around
here. Let's check it out!

182
00:08:46,375 --> 00:08:48,416
[MOA] Oh, yeah! I read
about it in a magazine!

183
00:08:48,500 --> 00:08:50,291
Hamburgers for sure
qualify as yummy!

184
00:08:50,375 --> 00:08:51,791
Is this the one?

185
00:08:51,875 --> 00:08:54,291
[CHUCHU]
Yes! That's Retoree for you!

186
00:08:54,375 --> 00:08:55,875
[RETOREE]
Awesome.

187
00:08:55,958 --> 00:08:58,500
I say we end practice for today
and go pay 'em a little visit!

188
00:08:58,583 --> 00:08:59,750
[MOA]
Sounds good to me!

189
00:08:59,833 --> 00:09:01,333
But, don't we...?

190
00:09:01,416 --> 00:09:03,625
You've gotta relax and take
it easy once in a while.

191
00:09:03,708 --> 00:09:05,625
We still have plenty
of time, pyuru.

192
00:09:05,708 --> 00:09:07,125
Totally.

193
00:09:07,208 --> 00:09:08,708
Oh. Okay.

194
00:09:08,791 --> 00:09:11,125
[CHUCHU]
Rushing won't do you any good.

195
00:09:11,208 --> 00:09:13,375
Yeah. I guess you're right.

196
00:09:16,083 --> 00:09:18,000
[CROW]
Yo! What's up?

197
00:09:18,083 --> 00:09:20,583
Man, this place never
changes, does it.

198
00:09:20,666 --> 00:09:23,541
Huh. I almost forgot.

199
00:09:23,625 --> 00:09:26,458
You used to work here
part-time as well, didn't you.

200
00:09:26,541 --> 00:09:27,541
[CROW]
Yep!

201
00:09:27,625 --> 00:09:29,000
And thanks to the
money I made here,

202
00:09:29,083 --> 00:09:33,333
I was able to get my hands
on my beloved Red Tomahawk.

203
00:09:33,416 --> 00:09:35,250
But, enough memory lane.

204
00:09:35,333 --> 00:09:37,958
So what was it you wanted
to talk to me about?

205
00:09:38,041 --> 00:09:39,500
Not now.

206
00:09:39,583 --> 00:09:41,666
I wanted to discuss it with you
later tonight. It's serious.

207
00:09:41,750 --> 00:09:43,000
For real?

208
00:09:43,083 --> 00:09:44,666
Why didn't we just talk
about this at the studio?

209
00:09:44,750 --> 00:09:46,000
Could've saved me
the trouble of coming

210
00:09:46,083 --> 00:09:49,000
all the way down here.
Anyway, is it just me?

211
00:09:49,083 --> 00:09:50,041
For now.

212
00:09:50,125 --> 00:09:51,666
But Aion will be
joining us shortly.

213
00:09:51,750 --> 00:09:53,416
As a protector of the Holy Land,

214
00:09:53,500 --> 00:09:56,000
this store is like
the underworld to him.

215
00:09:56,083 --> 00:09:58,375
Hence, he requires
resolve and courage

216
00:09:58,458 --> 00:10:02,416
just to be able to walk into
an establishment such as this.

217
00:10:02,500 --> 00:10:03,750
You knave!

218
00:10:09,166 --> 00:10:10,833
You're late, Aion. As expected.

219
00:10:10,916 --> 00:10:12,333
Gah!

220
00:10:14,333 --> 00:10:17,208
[AION] F-For a god to descend
upon a place like this is--

221
00:10:17,291 --> 00:10:19,708
[CROW] What are you,
some old, creepy witch?

222
00:10:19,791 --> 00:10:22,375
Seriously, what's up with
the weird wizard outfit?

223
00:10:22,458 --> 00:10:24,208
It's kind of embarrassing, dude.

224
00:10:24,291 --> 00:10:26,750
[AION] Any opinion concerning
my holy black clothes

225
00:10:26,833 --> 00:10:29,041
from a small, ant-like
rodent such as you

226
00:10:29,125 --> 00:10:31,250
means very little
to a god like me.

227
00:10:31,333 --> 00:10:32,125
Say what?

228
00:10:32,208 --> 00:10:33,208
[YAIBA]
We are all here now.

229
00:10:33,291 --> 00:10:34,250
Hence, we should speak.

230
00:10:34,333 --> 00:10:36,791
But where's Rom?

231
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:42,625
[YAIBA]
This actually concerns Rom.

232
00:10:42,708 --> 00:10:44,041
A CD?

233
00:10:48,750 --> 00:10:50,208
[CROW]
What's with this thing?


234
00:10:50,291 --> 00:10:52,250
I was helping the
president the other day--

235
00:10:52,333 --> 00:10:54,708
organizing, filing,
things of that nature--

236
00:10:54,791 --> 00:10:56,583
when I came across this.

237
00:10:56,666 --> 00:10:59,083
So what is it? A band demo?

238
00:10:59,166 --> 00:11:00,416
[YAIBA]
Indeed.

239
00:11:00,500 --> 00:11:01,625
[CROW]
Hm.

240
00:11:05,041 --> 00:11:06,500
[CROW]
What's this?

241
00:11:09,833 --> 00:11:11,083
[AION]
Interesting.

242
00:11:11,166 --> 00:11:13,916
Who is this Black Swan
spreading his dark wings?

243
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:16,250
These guys look super lame.

244
00:11:34,541 --> 00:11:36,250
Whoa, wait a sec!

245
00:11:36,333 --> 00:11:37,708
[AION]
Correct me if I'm wrong,

246
00:11:37,791 --> 00:11:39,541
but isn't this the force of
light that shines brightly

247
00:11:39,625 --> 00:11:41,500
in the hearts of girls
